cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.HC 

The paper discusses the development and testing of a wearable computer and computer-vision system for autonomous decision-making in field geology. This involves real-time image segmentation, acquisition of image mosaics, and determination of interesting points in the images. Therefore, the most likely category is computer vision (cs.CV). The system also involves robotics (cs.RO) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) for autonomous decision-making. The system is used for geological research (cs.GR) and involves human-computer interaction (cs.HC) through the wearable computer.
